review_content:
@aetrnl: Well, I like it, not that its current rating of 4.10 is that good anyway. I'll happily take this well-executed Russian leather effect over any Aventus-style Del Monte tinned fruit cocktail à la blowtorched bitumen roofing felt I've smelt. Wild guess--maybe don't spray it on as if you're trying to kill Godzilla. You're probably less likely to detest it if you walk through a mist of just a few sprays of it a few times. Four sprays total is probably enough. Spraying this directly onto anything may be excessive.

As for Kouros--fine, you don't have to like that either, but its position as an epoch-making classic is assured. That's why you get to rubbish it several decades after its release.

@ everyone: Rasputin layers this under CdG Zagorsk.

Expanding Bloom’s new age, tuberose lite formula, Gucci Bloom Ambrosia di Fiori makes for a more decadent wear than its predecessors with a base of whipped orris butter and soft, satiny Damascus rose, which here lends a textural element more than a distinctly rosy character. As is to be expected of a Bloom flanker, Ambrosia di Fiori is still very much a tuberose composition, now though, there is depth where once there was only gossamer petals and musk.

And that bottle, Christmas gift perfect!

@eauxSILLAGE

@Perfumedsecrets "The fragrances are available as 50 and 100 ml Eau de Toilette, except mandarin and violet one that will be available exclusively at Gucci flag stores as 100 ml Eau de Toilette."

I'm sorry but you'll have to visit a flag store to be able to sample it - that is unless you can find samples online or get them from a friend. :(


By the way, to add to the description that states that the most Flora by Gucci scents are available in 50ml and 100ml, I've also seen 30ml EDT bottles.

@scentfrommanna: Almairac's own house is called Parle moi de Parfum.
I am old enough to have experienced original Fahrenheit. He is clearly one of the greats.

Friends used to wear this and I would describe it as Guerlain-like (patch and vanilla in the base with peach on top). For me it's perfectly unisex.
